    "In these cases, customers often purchase multiple products to get rid of the delivery costs.",
    "When purchasing several products at a time, customers can either select multiple versions or copies of the same item or buy completely different items.",
    "According to Bai et al. (2023a) who analyse sales data of a leading flash-sales e-retailer, over 89% of the customers purchasing two products indeed purchase two different products.",
    "For these multi-purchase scenarios, choice models that are based on the single-purchase assumption might not perform well, see Feldman et al. (2021) and Wang et al. (2023d).",
    "Customer demand is typically estimated using choice models that rely on information regarding what customers do and do not purchase."
